  <h2 id="v0100">v0.10.0 — WebAuthn, Redis HA, DLQ & 47 Fixes</h2>

  <h3 id="v0100-webauthn">WebAuthn / Passkeys</h3>
  <p>
    Araxys now supports <strong>FIDO2 WebAuthn</strong> passwordless authentication with biometric passkeys. Full registration and authentication ceremonies are included:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>COSE key parsing</strong>: ES256 (ECDSA P-256), RS256 (RSA), and EdDSA (Ed25519) — zero external dependencies</li>
    <li><strong>Attestation verification</strong>: <code>none</code>, <code>indirect</code>, and <code>direct</code> attestation types supported</li>
    <li><strong>ChallengeStore</strong>: Server-side challenge storage with configurable TTL and <code>await</code> semantics — prevents replay</li>
    <li><strong>Sign count tracking</strong>: Monotonic counter verification to detect cloned authenticators</li>
    <li><strong>100% dependency coverage</strong>: CBOR parsing guards against oversized payloads and malformed input</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="code-block">
    <div class="code-block-header">
      <span class="code-block-lang">python</span>
      <button class="code-block-copy">Copy</button>
    </div>
    <pre><code set:html={`<span class="token-keyword">from</span> araxys <span class="token-keyword">import</span> AraxysConfig
<span class="token-keyword">from</span> araxys.core.config <span class="token-keyword">import</span> WebAuthnConfig

config = <span class="token-function">AraxysConfig</span>(
    <span class="token-param">secret_key</span>=<span class="token-string">"your-32-char-secret-key-here!!!!"</span>,
    <span class="token-param">webauthn</span>=<span class="token-function">WebAuthnConfig</span>(
        <span class="token-param">enabled</span>=<span class="token-bool">True</span>,
        <span class="token-param">rp_name</span>=<span class="token-string">"My App"</span>,
        <span class="token-param">rp_id</span>=<span class="token-string">"example.com"</span>,
        <span class="token-param">origin</span>=<span class="token-string">"https://example.com"</span>,
        <span class="token-param">challenge_ttl</span>=<span class="token-number">300</span>,
    ),
)`} /></pre>
  </div>

  <h3 id="v0100-redis">Redis Sentinel & Cluster</h3>
  <p>
    Araxys v0.10 introduces <strong>Redis high-availability modes</strong> for all backend services:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>RedisSentinelPool</strong>: Failover-aware connection pool that auto-discovers the current master via Sentinel monitoring. Reconnects automatically on failover events.</li>
    <li><strong>RedisClusterPool</strong>: Client-side sharded pool for Redis Cluster deployments, distributing keys across hash slots.</li>
    <li><strong>Mode routing</strong>: A single <code>mode</code> config field routes all Araxys backends to the correct pool — <code>"standalone"</code> (default), <code>"sentinel"</code>, or <code>"cluster"</code>.</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="code-block">
    <div class="code-block-header">
      <span class="code-block-lang">python</span>
      <button class="code-block-copy">Copy</button>
    </div>
    <pre><code set:html={`<span class="token-comment"># Sentinel mode — automatic failover</span>
config = <span class="token-function">AraxysConfig</span>(
    <span class="token-param">secret_key</span>=<span class="token-string">"..."</span>,
    <span class="token-param">redis</span>={
        <span class="token-string">"mode"</span>: <span class="token-string">"sentinel"</span>,
        <span class="token-string">"sentinels"</span>: [(<span class="token-string">"sentinel1"</span>, <span class="token-number">26379</span>), (<span class="token-string">"sentinel2"</span>, <span class="token-number">26379</span>)],
        <span class="token-string">"master_name"</span>: <span class="token-string">"araxys-master"</span>,
    },
)

<span class="token-comment"># Cluster mode — client-side sharding</span>
config = <span class="token-function">AraxysConfig</span>(
    <span class="token-param">secret_key</span>=<span class="token-string">"..."</span>,
    <span class="token-param">redis</span>={
        <span class="token-string">"mode"</span>: <span class="token-string">"cluster"</span>,
        <span class="token-string">"startup_nodes"</span>: [(<span class="token-string">"node1"</span>, <span class="token-number">6379</span>), (<span class="token-string">"node2"</span>, <span class="token-number">6379</span>)],
    },
)`} /></pre>
  </div>

  <h3 id="v0100-dlq">Webhook Dead-Letter Queue</h3>
  <p>
    Failed webhook deliveries are no longer silently discarded. The new <strong>Redis-backed Dead-Letter Queue (DLQ)</strong> ensures delivery durability:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Retry consumer</strong>: Background worker polls the DLQ and retries with exponential backoff</li>
    <li><strong>Admin API</strong>: <code>GET /admin/dlq/stats</code>, <code>POST /admin/dlq/retry</code>, <code>DELETE /admin/dlq/purge</code></li>
    <li><strong>Auto-purge TTL</strong>: Messages older than <code>dlq_ttl_seconds</code> are automatically expired</li>
    <li><strong>HKDF-derived signing key</strong>: Webhook HMAC keys are derived via HKDF-SHA256 from <code>secret_key</code> with module-specific info to prevent cross-module key reuse</li>
    <li><strong>SSRF Protection</strong>: 16 private IP ranges blocked (includes IPv4-mapped IPv6), <code>getaddrinfo</code> resolution to catch DNS rebinding, async DNS lookup, <code>follow_redirects=False</code>, delivery semaphore cap</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="code-block">
    <div class="code-block-header">
      <span class="code-block-lang">python</span>
      <button class="code-block-copy">Copy</button>
    </div>
    <pre><code set:html={`config = <span class="token-function">AraxysConfig</span>(
    <span class="token-param">secret_key</span>=<span class="token-string">"..."</span>,
    <span class="token-param">webhooks</span>=<span class="token-function">WebhookConfig</span>(
        <span class="token-param">webhook_url</span>=<span class="token-string">"https://hooks.example.com/araxys"</span>,
        <span class="token-param">dlq_enabled</span>=<span class="token-bool">True</span>,
        <span class="token-param">dlq_ttl_seconds</span>=<span class="token-number">604800</span>,   <span class="token-comment"># 7-day retention</span>
        <span class="token-param">dlq_max_retries</span>=<span class="token-number">5</span>,
        <span class="token-param">delivery_concurrency</span>=<span class="token-number">10</span>,  <span class="token-comment"># Semaphore cap</span>
    ),
)`} /></pre>
  </div>

  <h3 id="v0100-idle">Session Idle Timeout</h3>
  <p>
    Sessions now track <strong>last activity</strong> and can be expired after a configurable idle period — independent of the absolute <code>session_ttl</code>:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong><code>last_activity_at</code></strong>: New field on <code>SessionRecord</code>, updated on each authenticated request</li>
    <li><strong><code>touch_session()</code></strong>: Explicit method to refresh <code>last_activity_at</code> without creating a new session</li>
    <li><strong><code>idle_timeout_seconds</code></strong>: Configuration field — session is revoked if idle for longer than this value</li>
    <li><strong>Automatic idle expiry</strong>: Background cleanup loop now purges idle-expired sessions in addition to TTL-expired ones</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="code-block">
    <div class="code-block-header">
      <span class="code-block-lang">python</span>
      <button class="code-block-copy">Copy</button>
    </div>
    <pre><code set:html={`<span class="token-comment"># Touch session on each authenticated request</span>
<span class="token-decorator">@app.get</span>(<span class="token-string">"/dashboard"</span>)
<span class="token-keyword">async def</span> <span class="token-function">dashboard</span>(<span class="token-param">session_id</span>: <span class="token-builtin">str</span>):
    <span class="token-keyword">await</span> shield.session_manager.<span class="token-function">touch_session</span>(session_id)
    <span class="token-keyword">return</span> {<span class="token-string">"status"</span>: <span class="token-string">"ok"</span>}
<span class="token-comment"># Session auto-expires if idle for &gt; idle_timeout_seconds</span>`} /></pre>
  </div>

  <h3 id="v0100-audit">Security Audit (47 fixes)</h3>
  <p>Every module received hardening in v0.10.0. Key categories:</p>

